== Post-Meiji Restoration ==
''For the history of municipalities within the district, see {{ill|Higashiyamanashi District, Yamanashi|en|Higashiyamanashi District, Yamanashi|WD=Q5754165|lt=Higashiyamanashi District|1=Higashiyamanashi District, Yamanashi}} and {{ill|Nishiyamanashi District, Yamanashi|en|Nishiyamanashi District, Yamanashi|WD=Q11627865|lt=Nishiyamanashi District|1=Nishiyamanashi District, Yamanashi}}.''

* During the early Meiji period, the district's territories were distributed as follows (1 town, 147 villages):
** Former '''Higashiyamanashi District''' (94 villages) - under the control of Kofu Magistrate's Office, Isawa Magistrate's Office, and the {{ill|House of Tokugawa-Tayasu|ja|田安徳川家|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/House of Tokugawa-Tayasu|1=Tayasu House|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11576489}}.
** Former '''Nishiyamanashi District''' (1 town, 53 villages) - under the Kofu Magistrate's Office, Isawa Magistrate's Office, and Ichikawa Magistrate's Office.
* Meiji 2 (1869) - Yamanashi Prefecture was established from the Kofu region.
* Meiji 11 (1878) - The district was officially dissolved, with its areas reorganized into Higashiyamanashi and Nishiyamanashi Districts.

